Miss Alicia Larde.

603
00:38:49,119 --> 00:38:50,880
Miss Alicia Larde.
How do you do?

604
00:38:50,920 --> 00:38:52,840
Professor, please.
You and the governor.

605
00:38:55,079 --> 00:38:57,480
Wait, one second.
I'm sorry.

606
00:38:59,039 --> 00:39:00,440
I want a copy of this.

607
00:39:00,480 --> 00:39:02,639
First big date and all,
you know.

608
00:39:02,719 --> 00:39:05,639
So, you boys need
to look good.

609
00:39:07,079 --> 00:39:08,800
Which is not a state
you find yourselves in...

610
00:39:08,840 --> 00:39:11,880
altogether naturally.

611
00:39:14,320 --> 00:39:17,280
There. Better.

612
00:39:18,400 --> 00:39:21,239
- I'm surprising him.
- You just keep on surprising him.

613
00:39:21,320 --> 00:39:23,039
Professor.

614
00:39:38,559 --> 00:39:41,039
God must be a painter.

615
00:39:42,559 --> 00:39:44,320
Why else would we
have so many colors?

616
00:39:46,599 --> 00:39:49,280
So you're a painter?

617
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:51,960
That's not actually
what I said,

618
00:39:52,039 --> 00:39:54,679
but, yes-

619
00:39:54,760 --> 00:39:56,800
